The federal government has announced fresh five cases of COVID-19 in the country. This brings the total number of cases in the country to eight. According to the minister of health, Dr.Osagie Ehanire, who made the announcement on Wednesday, three of the new cases arrived from the United states while the remaining two came into the country from the United Kingdom (UK). He also disclosed that among the three from the US, two are Nigerians; a mother and her 6-week old baby. Furthermore, the two from the UK are both Nigerians. Details laterâ€¦